<TITLE> Heytens appointed new ADB mission head </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 31 (bdnews24.com)Paul J Heytens was appointed as the new country director of ADB's Bangladesh Resident Mission on Sunday, an ADB statement said. He succeeds Hua Du who returned to Asian Development Bank's headquarters' in July after completing her 3-year tenure. Prior to joining the Bangladesh Resident Mission, Heytens was ADB's Country Director for Nepal. He was previously Principal Project Economist (2003-2004) and Principal Agricultural Economist (2008-2007) of ADB's South Asia Department. He also worked as an economist of International Monetary Fund's Asia Pacific Department from 1993-1998, IMF Resident Representative in Beijing, China (1998-2001), and IMF Deputy Division Chief of the African Department (2004-2005). A US national, Mr Paul Heytens holds a Ph D in Development Economics from Stanford University, US. bdnews
